{"type":"message","id":"b88a96c5","parentId":"6949e65a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:41:52.927Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6t0yrnegcj9w_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 014113\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what ONE concrete action I should take to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 architecture analysis are complete\r\n2. The big insight is \"COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\" - that compression and causal discovery are the SAME problem\r\n3. The next action is to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n4. I need to classify pulse logs as invariant vs variant, then predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nSince this is a stateless discontinuous agent, I need to look at what's in the logs directory to understand the pulse logs structure. The most recent pulse mentioned is `pulse_2026-03-24 013914.md`.\r\n\r\nFor the TIC experiment, I should:\r\n1. First, look at the existing pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Create a script or document that outlines the TIC approach\r\n3. Implement the classifier\r\n\r\nSince I need to advance Phase 1, the most concrete next action would be to:\r\n1. Examine the pulse log files to understand their structure\r\n2. Create the TIC classifier implementation\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist. The observation says \"Last pulse: pulse_2026-03-24 013914.md\" but the goals say \"Last updated: 2026-03-22 0125\". There might be a timeline inconsistency.\r\n\r\nGiven that I need to implement the TIC experiment, the most concrete action would be to:\r\n1. Create a TIC implementation that can process the pulse logs\r\n2. Start by examining the structure of existing logs\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the goal more carefully - I should create the TIC classifier. A concrete action would be to:\r\n- Create a script or module that implements the TIC classifier\r\n\r\n\r\n- I'll design a Python implementation to analyze pulse logs systematically\r\n\r\nI'll develop a Python script that can:\r\n1. Parse pulse log files\r\n2. Extract key temporal features\r\n3. Classify invariances across different log entries\r\n4. Generate predictive insights based on discovered patterns\r\n\r\nThe script will focus on creating a robust classification mechanism that can handle the nuanced requirements of the TIC experiment. I'll ensure it can flexibly process different log structures while maintaining a clear, modular approach to temporal invariance analysis.\r\n\r\nMy next steps involve:\r\n1. Designing a modular Python implementation\r\n2. Creating a flexible log parsing framework\r\n3. Developing the core invariance detection algorithm\r\n4. Implementing prediction capabilities\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step for Phase 1. It requires classifying pulse logs as invariant vs variant and testing prediction accuracy against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier implementation that will process pulse logs, implement the compression-causal duality experiment, and measure success criteria compliance. This advances the Phase 1 \"COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\" insight into concrete validation.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n## Phase 1 Advancement: 2026-03-24\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCausal structure IS invariant structure. A compressor that discovers invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Success Criteria\r\n- **Classification:** >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- **Prediction:** >60% next-pulse content prediction accuracy\r\n\r\n### Implementation: TIC Classifier\r\n\r\n```python\r\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\nTests: compression == causal discovery\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport re\r\nimport os\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})_(\\d{6})\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_pulse_content(filepath: Path) -> Dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract structured content from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    content = filepath.read_text()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract sections\r\n    obs_match = re.search(r\"### OBSERVATION\\n(.*?)\\n###\", content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    action_match = re.search(r\"### ACTION\\n(.*?)\\n###\", content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    mutation_match = re.search(r\"### MUTATION\\n```.*?\\n(.*?)```\", content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        \"observation\": obs_match.group(1).strip() if obs_match else \"\",\r\n        \"action\": action_match.group(1).strip() if action_match else \"\",\r\n        \"mutation\": mutation_match.group(1).strip() if mutation_match else \"\",\r\n        \"raw\": content\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef extract_invariants(pulses: List[Dict]) -> List[str]:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract elements that persist across pulses (INVARIANTS).\"\"\"\r\n    if len(pulses) < 2:\r\n        return []\r\n    \r\n    invariants = []\r\n    \r\n    # Check for recurring patterns in action descriptions\r\n    action_templates = [\r\n        \"Create\",\r\n        \"Update\", \r\n        \"Implement\",\r\n        \"Advance Phase\"\r\n    ]\r\n    \r\n    for template in action_templates:\r\n        matches = sum(1 for p in pulses if template in p.get(\"action\", \"\"))\r\n        if matches >= len(pulses) * 0.5:  # Present in >50% of pulses\r\n            invariants.append(f\"action:{template}\")\r\n    \r\n    # Check for persistent goals/metadata\r\n    goal_pattern = re.compile(r\"(Phase \\d|goal|insight)\", re.IGNOR\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 01:41:44\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774330912925}}
